WEBVTT

00:00:06.639 --> 00:00:07.240
Sister Wang

00:00:07.599 --> 00:00:08.599
The usual three, please

00:00:08.720 --> 00:00:09.439
Got it, the usual three

00:00:13.039 --> 00:00:13.720
Lao Ma

00:00:14.240 --> 00:00:14.800
Zhang Da

00:00:14.960 --> 00:00:17.039
Zhao Dian and I are still at the docks checking Velipa

00:00:17.399 --> 00:00:18.320
The little punk probably knows

00:00:18.320 --> 00:00:19.480
what we're looking into is serious

00:00:19.559 --> 00:00:20.600
He only handed us paper receipts

00:00:20.839 --> 00:00:21.399
Nothing we can do

00:00:21.719 --> 00:00:23.399
Zhao Dian and I have to check each one

00:00:23.519 --> 00:00:24.120
I won't make it back

00:00:24.199 --> 00:00:24.800
Go ahead and eat without me

00:00:24.920 --> 00:00:26.199
You guys are working hard

00:00:26.280 --> 00:00:27.960
I'll grab a quick bite here and head back

00:00:28.039 --> 00:00:28.719
Alright, hanging up

00:00:28.920 --> 00:00:29.440
Okay

00:00:31.719 --> 00:00:33.759
Sister Wang, hold the soup

00:00:33.759 --> 00:00:34.560
Too late

00:00:34.719 --> 00:00:35.159
Okay

00:00:35.240 --> 00:00:36.200
I haven't even eaten yet

00:00:38.840 --> 00:00:39.799
The boss is here

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:41.119
What are you doing here?

00:00:41.520 --> 00:00:43.000
Let's eat first, I'm starving

00:00:44.679 --> 00:00:45.960
Fine, go ahead and eat

00:00:48.719 --> 00:00:49.320
Have some vinegar

00:00:49.520 --> 00:00:50.359
I don't want vinegar

00:00:50.600 --> 00:00:51.679
Add a little, it tastes better

00:00:54.840 --> 00:00:55.520
Have some chili

00:00:55.799 --> 00:00:56.439
No chili for me at all

00:00:56.439 --> 00:00:57.799
It's not spicy, not spicy at all

00:00:59.719 --> 00:01:01.039
Sorry, I put in too much

00:01:01.200 --> 00:01:01.960
Didn't you have something to discuss?

00:01:01.960 --> 00:01:02.560
Just spit it out

00:01:02.560 --> 00:01:04.480
You're piling on vinegar and chili

00:01:04.599 --> 00:01:05.760
Is there some new development?

00:01:08.040 --> 00:01:09.640
The nursing home's drug expenses are off

00:01:10.120 --> 00:01:11.159
Absurdly inflated

00:01:12.799 --> 00:01:13.680
In other words

00:01:14.040 --> 00:01:15.680
Either someone inside is skimming,

00:01:15.879 --> 00:01:17.319
deliberately reporting higher drug prices

00:01:17.760 --> 00:01:19.120
when the real cost is much less,

00:01:19.120 --> 00:01:20.400
pocketing the difference.

00:01:20.799 --> 00:01:23.480
Or someone is inflating prices on purpose

00:01:23.719 --> 00:01:25.920
to move money out disguised as drug buys.

00:01:26.239 --> 00:01:27.599
On the surface it looks like medical spending

00:01:27.719 --> 00:01:29.319
but it's actually funneling out funds

00:01:31.519 --> 00:01:32.719
So what you're saying is

00:01:34.560 --> 00:01:35.560
this nursing home

00:01:36.200 --> 00:01:38.359
is also part of A-Xin's money laundering

00:01:38.359 --> 00:01:40.159
scheme, right?

00:01:40.640 --> 00:01:42.319
Based on the leads we have so far

00:01:42.359 --> 00:01:43.400
it's very likely

00:01:44.159 --> 00:01:45.519
But what really matters is

00:01:46.319 --> 00:01:48.640
Fengmao, Xin Qili, the nursing home,

00:01:48.959 --> 00:01:51.359
where the money in this chain comes from

00:01:51.519 --> 00:01:52.319
and where it goes

00:01:59.799 --> 00:02:00.480
Sister Wang

00:02:01.040 --> 00:02:02.840
Bring a spoon, a spoon please

00:02:03.879 --> 00:02:05.799
This soup tastes kind of weird

00:02:07.079 --> 00:02:07.879
It's black chicken soup

00:02:08.520 --> 00:02:09.439
What weird taste could it have?

00:02:20.639 --> 00:02:22.159
I'll give you 500,000 in cash up front

00:02:22.759 --> 00:02:24.599
and I'll cover all future treatment costs

00:02:25.800 --> 00:02:26.960
Just hand over the evidence first

00:02:28.680 --> 00:02:30.400
I also want a guarantee for my safety

00:02:32.960 --> 00:02:34.439
You have to give me the evidence first

00:02:34.520 --> 00:02:35.960
before I can talk to Ruan Chen

00:02:37.159 --> 00:02:38.039
After that

00:02:38.240 --> 00:02:39.560
it's a tug-of-war between him and me

00:02:40.319 --> 00:02:41.759
No one will come after you

00:02:45.639 --> 00:02:47.039
If I hand over the evidence to you

00:02:47.560 --> 00:02:49.360
what if you turn around and sell me out?

00:02:58.479 --> 00:02:59.719
This deal

00:03:00.080 --> 00:03:01.319
is one you came to me about

00:03:02.520 --> 00:03:03.639
Right now, besides me

00:03:04.280 --> 00:03:05.319
you've got no one else to turn to

00:03:07.199 --> 00:03:08.599
I know what you're thinking

00:03:09.599 --> 00:03:10.800
But you have your own dilemma,

00:03:10.960 --> 00:03:11.960
and I have mine

00:03:12.960 --> 00:03:14.159
A mutually beneficial deal

00:03:14.800 --> 00:03:16.439
is the only way to put everyone at ease

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:17.719
Right?

00:03:26.159 --> 00:03:26.960
I trust you

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:28.919
In fifteen minutes

00:03:29.120 --> 00:03:30.599
I'll get the USB drive and give it to you

00:04:19.199 --> 00:04:19.959
That's a lot

00:04:22.439 --> 00:04:23.800
He's too scheming,

00:04:24.439 --> 00:04:25.480
which is never a good thing

00:04:28.079 --> 00:04:29.240
We can't let him live

00:04:31.079 --> 00:04:32.000
What about Luo Xiao?

00:04:36.319 --> 00:04:38.800
Luo Xiao is a lawyer

00:04:39.519 --> 00:04:40.560
All this stuff,

00:04:41.560 --> 00:04:43.000
he must've made copies

00:04:44.680 --> 00:04:47.720
Holding them as leverage against me

00:04:49.560 --> 00:04:50.240
Understood

00:04:51.279 --> 00:04:52.079
Don't move on him yet

00:04:54.759 --> 00:04:57.120
Wait till he launders the whole billion,

00:04:58.519 --> 00:04:59.360
then take care of him

00:05:00.399 --> 00:05:01.519
I'll send some men

00:05:01.920 --> 00:05:03.160
to grab Xin Youna first

00:05:03.279 --> 00:05:03.839
No

00:05:05.120 --> 00:05:06.560
Hospitals have too many eyes,

00:05:07.920 --> 00:05:09.680
and the cops are watching her

00:05:10.680 --> 00:05:13.759
Get Briefcase to handle it

00:05:28.759 --> 00:05:30.360
Do you know Tang Seng's surname?

00:05:31.040 --> 00:05:32.759
Tang Seng's surname is Tang.

00:05:35.319 --> 00:05:36.160
A long time ago,

00:05:37.120 --> 00:05:38.560
there was an old man named Yu Gong.

00:05:38.879 --> 00:05:40.759
There was a huge mountain outside his door.

00:05:41.319 --> 00:05:43.079
He said, I'm gonna move this mountain,

00:05:43.519 --> 00:05:45.120
generation after generation will move it.

00:05:45.759 --> 00:05:47.560
By Tang Seng's generation,

00:05:47.879 --> 00:05:48.519
they moved that mountain aside,

00:05:48.519 --> 00:05:50.399
and found a monkey trapped underneath.

00:05:51.439 --> 00:05:52.480
So what's Tang Seng's surname?

00:05:52.600 --> 00:05:53.360
Monkey?

00:05:53.720 --> 00:05:54.680
It's Yu!

00:05:55.680 --> 00:05:57.040
Tang Seng is Yu Gong's grandson.

00:05:57.399 --> 00:05:58.720
That'd make him Monk Yu.

00:05:58.879 --> 00:05:59.519
Exactly.

00:06:00.279 --> 00:06:02.279
The idiom "surviving disaster" refers to Sun Wukong.

00:06:03.160 --> 00:06:05.399
Bro, where's our contact?

00:06:05.680 --> 00:06:07.040
Watch what you say.

00:06:08.519 --> 00:06:09.959
"Contact" this, "contact" that.

00:06:10.600 --> 00:06:11.839
You'll blow our cover.

00:06:13.399 --> 00:06:14.160
What's wrong?

00:06:30.240 --> 00:06:31.199
Did I say we're leaving?

00:06:32.360 --> 00:06:33.360
Did I say I was leaving?

00:06:36.160 --> 00:06:37.120
I...

00:07:09.600 --> 00:07:10.240
Yao.

00:07:27.959 --> 00:07:29.079
Hold on, hold on.

00:07:35.439 --> 00:07:36.120
Yao.

00:07:38.360 --> 00:07:39.240
That's so much money.

00:07:41.120 --> 00:07:42.519
They really weren't lying.

00:07:45.279 --> 00:07:46.000
A hundred grand.

00:07:47.040 --> 00:07:49.079
Hilarious. Looks like a damn idiot.

00:07:49.079 --> 00:07:50.240
Never seen the world.

00:07:50.399 --> 00:07:52.040
There'll be plenty more hundred grands.

00:07:52.680 --> 00:07:53.480
Let me see the photo.

00:07:56.560 --> 00:07:57.480
She's pretty good-looking.

00:07:58.720 --> 00:07:59.360
Yeah.

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:00.800
What a shame.

00:08:02.399 --> 00:08:03.040
Where's the other one?

00:08:03.199 --> 00:08:04.040
Weren't there two photos?

00:08:07.319 --> 00:08:08.000
No.

00:08:08.199 --> 00:08:09.160
Just one person?

00:08:10.439 --> 00:08:11.879
Then let's handle this one first.

00:08:49.039 --> 00:08:50.639
We didn't find Velipa on any product list,

00:08:50.759 --> 00:08:52.759
but we found that A-Xin once

00:08:52.840 --> 00:08:54.840
delivered medications to this nursing home.

00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:57.320
On the surface, all legal, regulated drugs.

00:08:57.440 --> 00:08:59.080
But my guess is, Velipa,

00:08:59.159 --> 00:09:01.240
along with other illegal drugs,

00:09:01.320 --> 00:09:02.399
were mixed in among them.

00:09:03.159 --> 00:09:04.360
Which means

00:09:04.600 --> 00:09:06.120
A-Xin likely helped the nursing home

00:09:06.120 --> 00:09:07.559
transport unapproved drugs.

00:09:07.960 --> 00:09:09.679
That explains why the medical records

00:09:09.679 --> 00:09:10.440
and payment records

00:09:10.440 --> 00:09:12.759
don't match A-You's actual medication.

00:09:15.360 --> 00:09:16.799
So this nursing home

00:09:16.799 --> 00:09:18.240
actually keeps two sets of books.

00:09:18.600 --> 00:09:20.440
One for show: standard drug treatment,

00:09:20.559 --> 00:09:21.960
with reasonable, regular fees.

00:09:22.320 --> 00:09:23.360
The other, internal:

00:09:23.600 --> 00:09:24.759
illegal drug treatment.

00:09:25.000 --> 00:09:26.519
The real costs and medication details

00:09:26.600 --> 00:09:27.559
can't see the light of day.

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:30.799
A-Xin is tied to the underground bank,

00:09:30.879 --> 00:09:32.799
the nursing home is cooking the books,

00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:35.159
A-Xin delivers illegal drugs for them,

00:09:35.240 --> 00:09:36.840
A-Xin's sister lives at the nursing home,

00:09:36.919 --> 00:09:37.879
using those illegal drugs.

00:09:37.960 --> 00:09:39.320
Connect all these clues together...

00:09:42.799 --> 00:09:43.440
Dian.

00:09:44.120 --> 00:09:44.759
Move out.

00:09:55.120 --> 00:09:55.799
Yao.

00:09:57.000 --> 00:09:58.120
After all these years,

00:09:58.679 --> 00:09:59.759
nothing's really changed.

00:10:01.360 --> 00:10:02.279
What do you mean nothing's changed?

00:10:03.200 --> 00:10:04.080
A lot has changed.

00:10:05.200 --> 00:10:05.840
We've got food when we want it,

00:10:05.919 --> 00:10:06.799
clothes when we want them.

00:10:09.039 --> 00:10:10.080
Get yourself some new shoes.

00:10:11.799 --> 00:10:12.799
Where would I get shoes?

00:10:13.240 --> 00:10:14.840
So much going on, no time.

00:10:15.320 --> 00:10:16.399
I've got shoes on, don't I?

00:10:20.480 --> 00:10:21.200
My feet are freezing.

00:10:21.679 --> 00:10:23.679
Where? Nobody sells shoes around here.

00:10:26.480 --> 00:10:27.840
So much fuss.

00:10:32.759 --> 00:10:33.320
Sweetie.

00:10:33.720 --> 00:10:35.720
Listen to the sound of gold clinking.

00:10:35.840 --> 00:10:36.720
Doesn't it sound nice?

00:10:38.759 --> 00:10:39.720
The baby likes it.

00:10:39.799 --> 00:10:41.279
Uncle will give you a few more. Daddy...

00:10:42.679 --> 00:10:43.399
Xiao.

00:10:44.279 --> 00:10:45.360
I couldn't get through on your phone.

00:10:45.480 --> 00:10:46.960
Mr. Jin's been sitting here for a while.

00:10:47.720 --> 00:10:48.799
I need to talk to Xiao about something.

00:10:49.120 --> 00:10:50.000
Ladies, please go ahead and eat.

00:10:50.240 --> 00:10:50.879
Grown in our own greenhouse.

00:10:50.879 --> 00:10:51.799
Very healthy, very healthy.

00:10:51.879 --> 00:10:52.559
Go on, eat up.

00:10:53.840 --> 00:10:55.399
Open your mouth, here.

00:11:00.080 --> 00:11:01.120
You... Xiao.

00:11:01.879 --> 00:11:03.639
How did you find this place?

00:11:03.919 --> 00:11:04.679
Xiao.

00:11:04.960 --> 00:11:06.759
I was a bit out of line before.

00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:07.919
Wasn't thinking straight.

00:11:08.200 --> 00:11:09.480
This damn place is huge.

00:11:09.559 --> 00:11:10.480
Which one?

00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:12.919
You.

00:11:16.759 --> 00:11:17.919
Hi, can I ask you something?

00:11:18.320 --> 00:11:19.559
Where's 306B?

00:11:20.519 --> 00:11:22.440
Two floors up, then right out the door.

00:11:23.120 --> 00:11:23.840
All the way to the end.

00:11:24.360 --> 00:11:25.120
Okay, thanks.

00:11:25.720 --> 00:11:26.679
Two floors up, let's go.

00:11:26.799 --> 00:11:29.080
Yao, this hospital is huge.

00:11:29.200 --> 00:11:30.120
Yeah, pretty nice.

00:11:30.279 --> 00:11:31.960
Let's stay here a couple of days.

00:11:33.200 --> 00:11:33.919
You stay by yourself, then.

00:11:34.039 --> 00:11:34.799
I can't do that.

00:11:35.840 --> 00:11:37.559
I really was a bit out of line before.

00:11:38.159 --> 00:11:40.559
Bringing all this up at the office.

00:11:40.720 --> 00:11:42.440
I broke some of your rules, Xiao.

00:11:42.639 --> 00:11:43.919
Xiao, please forgive me.

00:11:45.159 --> 00:11:47.679
Mr. Jin, it's not about rules.

00:11:47.919 --> 00:11:49.440
What do you actually want from me?

00:11:51.879 --> 00:11:53.000
To make money.

00:11:53.360 --> 00:11:56.039
Help me find a way, Xiao.

00:11:56.559 --> 00:11:58.159
I told you, in your situation,

00:11:58.240 --> 00:12:00.039
you need a financial advisor.

00:12:00.440 --> 00:12:02.399
I'm a lawyer. I can't help you with that.

00:12:03.720 --> 00:12:07.039
Xiao, precisely because you're a lawyer,

00:12:07.320 --> 00:12:08.600
that's why I came to you.

00:12:09.399 --> 00:12:10.679
I'll be honest with you.

00:12:11.000 --> 00:12:12.200
I've got some money

00:12:12.639 --> 00:12:13.679
that's not exactly clean.

00:12:13.799 --> 00:12:14.720
So,

00:12:14.919 --> 00:12:18.360
I need you to help move it around.

00:12:18.879 --> 00:12:20.080
Tou said

00:12:20.200 --> 00:12:23.039
he trusts you a hundred percent.

00:12:23.240 --> 00:12:26.159
The cut, the percentage,

00:12:26.320 --> 00:12:27.600
all negotiable, all negotiable.

00:12:30.679 --> 00:12:31.840
Sorry, Mr. Jin.

00:12:32.600 --> 00:12:33.559
Lately I've been

00:12:34.480 --> 00:12:35.559
swamped with stuff.

00:12:36.240 --> 00:12:37.000
From now on,

00:12:37.759 --> 00:12:39.120
don't bother me if you have no business.

00:12:39.679 --> 00:12:41.120
And don't bother me if you do, either.

00:12:42.399 --> 00:12:43.440
I'm going to spend time with my kid.

00:12:43.720 --> 00:12:44.720
So I won't keep you company.

00:12:46.600 --> 00:12:47.440
I won't see you out.